broadleaf
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Griselinia littoralis</i>, with foliage palatable to stock and with timber commonly used for fenceposts or battens. [occ. used for Gr lucida and some native coprosmas.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka kapuka, papauma, pukatea
