Quote:  There are few trees in the [Otago] bush so conspicuous or so well known as the broad-leaf....It grows to a height of fifty or sixty feet, and a diameter of from three to six; the bark is coarse and fibrous, and the leaves a beautiful deep green of great brilliancy.
Notes:  (Morris)

